{"word":"χῶρος","slug":"χῶρος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>χῶρος</b></el> <el>(χῶρος, ὁ,) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a piece of ground, ground, place</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a land, country</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>lands, places</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>land, an estate</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>the country</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>rus</el>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>deriv.</a> uncertain\n"}]}